    "(Weiss, 1999) Each agent decides in each time step and works along with the other agents to achieve an individual predetermined goal.",
    "On the one hand, cooperative multi-agent systems are ones in which several agents attempt to solve tasks jointly or to maximize utility.",
    "(Panait & Luke, 2005) On the other hand, competitive agents have contradicting goals and compete against each other.",
    "Most work in MARL focuses on fully cooperative settings (Foerster et al. 2017).",
